@startuml cv-ingest-flow
title CV Ingest — Upload & Indexing Flow

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderThickness 1
skinparam noteBorderColor #888
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #555

actor       "User"           as client
participant "falcon-cv-ingest"    as ingest  #D0E8FF
participant "MongoDB"             as mongo   #E8F5E9
participant "MinIO"               as minio   #FFF3E0
participant "Embeddings API"      as embed   #F3E5F5
participant "Qdrant"              as qdrant  #E8EAF6
participant "NATS JetStream"      as nats    #FCE4EC

== 1 · Prepare Upload ==

client  -> ingest   : POST /cv/prepare\n{ filename }
note right of ingest
  No auth required.
  User identity not yet known.
end note

ingest  -> mongo    : insert PersistedCV\n{ status: pending_upload }
mongo  --> ingest   : ok

ingest  -> minio    : PresignedPutObject(bucket, key, 15 min)
minio  --> ingest   : presigned PUT URL

ingest --> client   : 201 { cv_id, upload_url, expires_at }

== 2 · Direct Upload to MinIO (client → MinIO, bypassing ingest) ==

client  -> minio    : PUT <upload_url>\nbody: <cv.docx bytes>
note right of minio
  Client uploads directly.
  falcon-cv-ingest never touches
  the raw bytes in this step.
end note
minio  --> client   : 200 OK

== 3 · Trigger Indexing ==

client  -> ingest   : POST /cv/:id/index\n{ email }
note right of ingest
  User provides email here.
  email is stored as user_id.
end note
ingest  -> mongo    : get PersistedCV by id
mongo  --> ingest   : PersistedCV{ status: pending_upload | uploaded }
ingest  -> mongo    : update status → indexing
ingest --> client   : 202 Accepted { status: "indexing" }

note over ingest
  Processing continues async
  in a background goroutine.
end note

== 4 · Indexing Pipeline (async) ==

group Extract
  ingest  -> minio    : GetObject(bucket, key)
  minio  --> ingest   : io.Reader (docx bytes)
  ingest  -> ingest   : extractText()\nunzip word/document.xml\nstrip XML tags
end group

group Embed
  ingest  -> embed    : POST /v1/embeddings\n{ input: text, model: bge-m3 }
  embed  --> ingest   : []float32 (1536 dims)
end group

group Index
  ingest  -> qdrant   : PUT /collections/cvs/points\n{ id, vector, payload }
  qdrant --> ingest   : ok
end group

group Persist & Notify
  ingest  -> mongo    : update status → indexed\nqdrant_id, updated_at
  ingest  -> nats     : publish "cv.indexed"\n{ cv_id, user_id, qdrant_id }
end group

== 5 · Downstream (falcon-dispatch) ==

nats    -> "falcon-dispatch" : consume "cv.indexed"
note right
  Dispatch now knows a new CV
  vector is available in Qdrant
  for future project matching.
end note

== Error Path ==

note over ingest
  Any step can fail.
  On failure: status → failed, error saved in MongoDB.
  Client can retry POST /cv/:id/index at any time.
end note

@enduml
